                     •
                  -Maſtix, wherein to the apprehenſion of ſome eminent men: he in effect denied the ſcriptures to be the word of God, and much diſcourſe, and great complaint there was about it, in ſo much as Collonel Leighs Committee had it brought before them, where it was my lot to be, when the paſſage concerning the Scriptures was read openly by one, thatamongſt others, informed againſt it: and where it was called a moſt impious, blaſphemous Book, and ordered to be ſeized, all of them immediatly;
